INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES (721, 432, '_aviaLayoutBuilderCleanData', '[av_slideshow size=\'no scaling\' animation=\'slide\' autoplay=\'false\' interval=\'5\']\r\n[av_slide id=\'481\']\r\n\r\n\r\n[/av_slideshow]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock]\r\n<h1 class="portpagefeatureh1">Emissions: 0. The Future: 1.</h1>\r\n<p class="portpagedatetext avia-align-center"><span style="color: #888888;">Hyundai becomes the first automaker to begin commercial production of a hydrogen-powered vehicle.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<img class="portpagedividerarrow avia_image avia-align-center" alt="divider arrow" src="/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/sectionDividerArrowGraphicDkGray.png" />\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock]\r\nIn January 2013, we became the first automaker to begin commercial production of a hydrogen-powered vehicle. That’s when production of the Hyundai Motor ix35 Fuel Cell began at our Ulsan manufacturing plant in Korea.\r\n\r\nInstead of burning hydrogen like gasoline as in previous hydrogen cars, fuel cells operate by converting hydrogen into electricity to power the motor and all other systems. The 136-hp electric motor can reach a maximum speed of 99 mph. Most importantly for the environment, the only by-product of the ix35 Fuel Cell is water vapor. A zero-emissions car. For this reason, the vehicle doesn’t have a tailpipe or engine noise. Otherwise it has the looks, versatility and performance of the gas-powered ix35, which shares the Tucson platform.\r\n\r\nWith a total capacity of 12.4 lbs., two heavily armored hydrogen storage tanks enable the vehicle to travel 369 miles on a single charge, which is stored in a lithium-ion polymer battery. Unlike plug-in electric vehicles that take hours to recharge, refueling the ix35 Fuel Cell only takes a few minutes via a pump.\r\n\r\nThe ix35 Fuel Cell is the latest generation of our family of fuel cell-powered electric vehicles (FCEV). Since we began researching and developing fuel cells in 1998, Hyundai has become a world leader in the development of the technology.  We’ve signed contracts to lease the ix35 Fuel Cell to municipal fleets in Scandinavian countries, and the first 15 cars were delivered to the City of Copenhagen in June.  As the technology becomes more accessible, our goal is to begin selling the vehicle to individual buyers in 2015 - a big step forward to an emission-free future.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock]\r\n<div id="sharemenuholder"></div>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock]\r\n<p class="portpagerelstoriestext avia-align-center"><span style="color: #888888;">RELATED STORIES</span></p>\r\n\r\n<img class="portpagedividerarrow avia_image avia-align-center" alt="divider arrow" src="/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/sectionDividerArrowGraphicDkGray.png" />\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_portfolio categories=\'48\' columns=\'4\' items=\'4\' contents=\'excerpt\' preview_mode=\'auto\' image_size=\'portfolio\' linking=\'\' sort=\'no\' paginate=\'no\']\r\n\r\n') ; 
