INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (440, 1, '2013-10-23 20:43:27', '2013-10-23 20:43:27', '[av_slideshow size=\'no scaling\' animation=\'slide\' autoplay=\'false\' interval=\'5\']\r\n[av_slide id=\'554\']\r\n[/av_slideshow]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock]\r\n<h1 class="portpagefeatureh1">Zombies Take Manhattan.</h1>\r\n<p class="portpagedatetext avia-align-center"><span style="color: #888888;">Watch our Walking Dead highlights from 2013 New York Comic Con.</span></p>\r\n<img class="portpagedividerarrow avia_image avia-align-center" alt="divider arrow" src="/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/sectionDividerArrowGraphicDkGray.png" />\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock ]\r\nA horde of 130,000 people descended upon Manhattan’s Jacob Javits Center for the 2013 New York Comic Con. One of the most anticipated events during the popular convention was the tenth anniversary of <i>The Walking Dead</i>.  Zombie aficionados swarmed the booth, which featured the winning fan-designed Hyundai Zombie Survival Machine, created with our <i>Walking Dead</i> Chop Shop app.  Attendees were able to have their photos taken with our undead-proof Santa Fe and even get behind the wheel.\r\n\r\nThere was even a separate <i>Walking Dead</i> gallery near the Javitz Center, which held an exhibit featuring artwork and behind-the-scenes memorabilia.  The gallery also hosted a premiere screening of the documentary “Decade of Dead,” presented by Hyundai.\r\n\r\nYou can watch highlights from NYCC and <i>The Walking Dead</i> gallery below.\r\n\r\nThe Walking Dead Chop Shop NYCC Recap\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/PymK0g3dgHA?rel=0" height="360" width="640" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">The Walking Dead Chop Shop NYCC Gallery and Party</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/jZ5FicAa8JM?rel=0" height="360" width="640" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe></p>\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[av_