INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (556, 1, '2013-11-01 15:37:51', '2013-11-01 22:37:51', '[av_slideshow size=\'no scaling\' animation=\'slide\' autoplay=\'false\' interval=\'5\']\n[av_slide id=\'552\']\n\n[/av_slideshow]\n\n[av_textblock]\n<h1 class="portpagefeatureh1">At NY Comic Con, We Unveil Our Sharpest-Looking Zombie Survival Machine Yet.</h1>\n<p class="portpagedatetext avia-align-center"><span style="color: #888888;">The fan-designed Santa Fe Zombie Survival Machine comes to life at NYCC.</span></p>\n<img class="portpagedividerarrow avia_image avia-align-center" alt="divider arrow" src="/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/sectionDividerArrowGraphicDkGray.png" />\n[/av_textblock]\n\n[av_textblock]\nKnife blades. Razor-wired windows. A samurai sword. <i>The Walking Dead</i> and zombie fans found their dream ride at NY Comic Con 2013: a Hyundai Santa Fe Zombie Survival Machine designed by Anson Kuo.\n\nKuo’s design – the “Santa Fleeee” – was picked as the winner out of more than 82,500 fan submissions on <i>The Walking Dead</i> Chop Shop configurator app. When he set out to build the ultimate Zombie Survival Machine, Kuo first looked to his driveway for inspiration. After recently purchasing an all-new Santa Fe Sport, Kuo decided to design his “zombie-mobile” based on his own car.\n\n“My main design goal was to make the vehicle as stealthy and spacious as possible,” said Kuo. “I knew knives and blades would be the best bet for weaponry – they could slice and dice the zombies without releasing any ammunition. Basing the design on the Santa Fe allows space for extra passengers as well as weapons, supplies, and all the other necessary items needed during a real zombie apocalypse.”\n\nGalpin Auto Sports (GAS) brought the Hyundai Santa Fe Zombie Survival Machine to life, which featured three machine guns, aluminum armor and an automatic crossbow. Comic Con attendees were able to have their pictures taken with the Zombie Survival Machine and even got to get behind the wheel.\n\n“We’re excited to see Anson’s Zombie Survival Machine debut at New York Comic Con,” said creator/writer Robert Kirkman. “This is a great addition to the celebration of the 10<sup>th</sup> Anniversary of <em>The Walking Dead</em>.”\n\nAlong with the Chop Shop winner, we commemorated our two-year relationship with <i>The Walking Dead</i> by presenting a documentary “A Decade Of Dead,” which premiered at Comic Con.\n\nWatch the contest-winning design become an undead-annihilating reality in the video below.\n\n<iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/0sdPBh9vs-s?rel=0" height="360" width="640" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe>\n[/av_textblock]\n\n[av_textblock]\n<div id="sharemenuholder"></div>\n[/av_textblock]\n\n[av_textblock]\n<p class="portpagerelstoriestext avia-align-center"><span style="color: #888888;">RELATED STORIES</span></p>\n<img class="portpagedividerarrow avia_image avia-align-center" alt="divider arrow" src="/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/sectionDividerArrowGraphicDkGray.png" />\n[/av_textblock]\n\n[av_portfolio categories=\'50,36\' columns=\'4\' items=\'4\' contents=\'excerpt\' preview_mode=\'auto\' image_size=\'portfolio\' linking=\'\' sort=\'no\' paginate=\'no\']', 'NY Comic Con - Sharpest-Looking Zombie Survival Machine Yet.', 'The fan-designed Santa Fe Zombie Survival Machine comes to life at NYCC.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '444-autosave-v1', '', '', '2013-11-01 15:37:51', '2013-11-01 22:37:51', '', 444, 'http://192.237.219.147/444-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
